  When a TypeScript caller sends `{ fts: false, ftsTokenizer: "x" }` or `{ vector: false, vectorEmbedder: "x" }`, this conversion accepts the object but silently discards the supplied tokenizer/embedder because the Rust sub-object is only constructed when the boolean is true. That means `configureProjections` succeeds while `read.projections` returns a different spec, so the napi boundary should reject these inconsistent flat shapes.
